column1: # Precipitation and Potential evaporation data derived from CSIRO AWAP data:

# The CSIRO data made available under the conditions of the Creative Commons
# Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 License:
# http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/
# AWAP References:
# Raupach MR
# Australian Water Availability Project (AWAP): CSIRO Marine and Atmospheric
# Research Component: Final Report for Phase 3. CAWCR Technical Report
# Raupach MR
# Australian Water Availability Project. CSIRO Marine and Atmospheric Research
# Canberra
# AWAP Grids processed the JSON catchment boundary (low resolution boundry for
# a dynamic map on the web) from the Hydrological Reference Stations project:
# http://www.bom.gov.au/water/hrs/ to produce the catchment average P and PE
# data here from the CSIRO data.
# Streamflow data from the Bureau of Meterology Water Data Online service
# which was made available under the Creative Commons Attribution license:
# http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/au/ by Icon Water Limited
# See: http://www.bom.gov.au/waterdata/
# Daily (9am to 9am) steamflow data (ML/day) was downloaded
# catchment area (130km^2) to get mm/day and aggregated to monthly.
# Processing performed by Andrew MacDonald (2016).
# Monthly data for: Cotter River at Gingera (410730)
# Catchment area: 130km^2.
